source.name: Trade Capacity Building Database
source.description: The database provides funding levels of U.S. Trade Capacity Building (TCB) activities designed to promote economic growth through international trade in developing countries and transition economies. U.S. TCB activities have received a higher profile since the 2001 WTO Ministerial in Doha and their increased funding enables the U.S. Government to fulfill its pledges of support for free trade areas and trade liberalization.
